1460
01:09:56,821 --> 01:09:58,365
Who?

1461
01:09:58,448 --> 01:10:00,283
- Me.
- You?

1462
01:10:00,325 --> 01:10:01,785
Yeah. Well, all of us.

1463
01:10:01,826 --> 01:10:04,079
Really with me more
than the girls, even.

1464
01:10:04,120 --> 01:10:05,246
Why? Because you're a boy?

1465
01:10:05,330 --> 01:10:07,582
Yeah. Because--yeah.
I mean, some--

1466
01:10:07,665 --> 01:10:09,125
What the hell
happened to them?

1467
01:10:09,209 --> 01:10:11,252
Somebody had to make
her happy, right?

1468
01:10:11,294 --> 01:10:14,506
Guess what? I tried.
Believe me, I tried.

1469
01:10:14,589 --> 01:10:18,259
That cloud, that--
that veil of disappointment...

1470
01:10:18,343 --> 01:10:20,428
I could never make it go away.

1471
01:10:20,512 --> 01:10:23,098
I could never crack
that sadness there.

1472
01:10:23,181 --> 01:10:25,266
So you know
what I'm talking about.

1473
01:10:25,308 --> 01:10:26,810
Yes, I do.

1474
01:10:26,851 --> 01:10:28,061
And I also know that...

1475
01:10:28,144 --> 01:10:31,106
she wouldn't have needed anything
from me if she got it--

1476
01:10:31,189 --> 01:10:33,566
- We also have a lovely--
- Walk away!

1477
01:10:33,650 --> 01:10:35,068
Just walk away.

1478
01:10:35,151 --> 01:10:37,612
She wouldn't have needed
anything from me...

1479
01:10:37,696 --> 01:10:39,239
if she got it from you.

1480
01:10:39,322 --> 01:10:40,824
- Is that right?
- Yes, that's right.

1481
01:10:40,907 --> 01:10:43,326
And I'm tired of feeling
like the fuckin' failure here...

1482
01:10:43,368 --> 01:10:45,161
'cause I'm not the one
who failed her, you are.

1483
01:10:45,245 --> 01:10:47,414
You are. You never cared.

1484
01:10:47,497 --> 01:10:49,249
You just went about
your business...

1485
01:10:49,332 --> 01:10:51,292
and, ''Oh, everything will
work out fine in the end.''

1486
01:10:51,376 --> 01:10:54,629
But you know what? It doesn't.
It doesn't work like that.

1487
01:10:54,713 --> 01:10:57,173
You have to--
you have to care.

1488
01:10:57,215 --> 01:11:00,301
You have to try
and give a shit. Huh?

1489
01:11:00,385 --> 01:11:02,137
Look at that letter.

1490
01:11:02,220 --> 01:11:06,725
I mean, she was screaming for you,
and you didn't hear it.

1491
01:11:06,808 --> 01:11:08,268
And now you're surprised?

1492
01:11:08,351 --> 01:11:10,103
Forty years later, your wife is--

1493
01:11:10,186 --> 01:11:12,313
God knows where she is--
trying to figure out...

1494
01:11:12,355 --> 01:11:14,941
why her life didn't work out
like she planned...

1495
01:11:15,025 --> 01:11:18,445
and you think that's got
nothing to do with you, huh?

1496
01:11:18,528 --> 01:11:21,156
It's got everything
to do with you.

1497
01:11:21,197 --> 01:11:23,908
You didn't do your job.
That's right.

1498
01:11:23,992 --> 01:11:26,327
You didn't do your job.

1499
01:11:47,390 --> 01:11:50,977
Ohh!

1500
01:11:51,061 --> 01:11:52,812
Uhh!

1501
01:11:59,569 --> 01:12:00,612
Hey.

1502
01:12:06,242 --> 01:12:10,580
What a waste of a good steak.

1503
01:12:10,663 --> 01:12:12,415
I'm an asshole.

1504
01:12:12,499 --> 01:12:14,709
- No.
- Yeah, yeah.

1505
01:12:14,751 --> 01:12:16,252
Listen, I...

1506
01:12:16,336 --> 01:12:18,421
I had no right saying all that.

1507
01:12:18,505 --> 01:12:19,839
- No.
- No, no, I didn't.

1508
01:12:19,923 --> 01:12:22,425
No, you're entitled.

1509
01:12:22,509 --> 01:12:26,262
And I'm gonna tell you
something else.

1510
01:12:26,346 --> 01:12:29,933
Maybe you're right.

1511
01:12:30,016 --> 01:12:34,270
Maybe I could've done better,
maybe I should've...

1512
01:12:34,354 --> 01:12:36,398
but I didn't.

1513
01:12:36,439 --> 01:12:38,483
So you know what?

1514
01:12:43,029 --> 01:12:44,989
I'm sorry.

1515
01:12:58,545 --> 01:13:00,171
OK.

1516
01:13:31,161 --> 01:13:34,122
You think the girls
are worried about us?

1517
01:13:34,164 --> 01:13:36,458
I think they'll be all right.

1518
01:13:36,499 --> 01:13:38,960
Unh. Do you know...

1519
01:13:39,002 --> 01:13:42,797
that was the first time
since Roosevelt died...

1520
01:13:42,839 --> 01:13:46,968
that I danced with someone
besides your mother?

1521
01:13:47,010 --> 01:13:48,470
And?

1522
01:13:48,511 --> 01:13:51,639
I didn't like it. It felt wrong--

1523
01:13:51,681 --> 01:13:53,975
wrong skin, wrong smell.

1524
01:13:54,017 --> 01:13:56,644
The height, her hands.

1525
01:13:56,686 --> 01:13:58,980
Didn't feel right.

1526
01:14:02,525 --> 01:14:06,571
Oh, what's she doing, Benny?

1527
01:14:08,656 --> 01:14:11,743
She's gonna live by herself?

1528
01:14:11,826 --> 01:14:15,955
She's gonna find someone else
she likes better?

1529
01:14:17,332 --> 01:14:18,625
Now?

1530
01:14:20,835 --> 01:14:25,298
You know, we're not kids anymore,
your mother and me.

1531
01:14:25,382 --> 01:14:29,511
You want to change your life,
do it when you're young.

1532
01:14:29,552 --> 01:14:31,930
Ugh! I don't know.

1533
01:14:32,013 --> 01:14:36,101
I don't know what she wants.
I don't know what I did.

1534
01:14:36,184 --> 01:14:37,769
I don't know anything.

1535
01:14:37,852 --> 01:14:42,941
Ahh, unh!

1536
01:14:43,024 --> 01:14:47,112
Are your stars moving around
all cock-eyed?

1537
01:14:47,195 --> 01:14:48,613
Yep.

1538
01:14:48,697 --> 01:14:50,782
Me, too.

1539
01:14:50,865 --> 01:14:53,785
Oh, you're a bad influence,
sonny boy.

1540
01:14:53,868 --> 01:14:55,954
You made your old man drunk.

1541
01:14:56,037 --> 01:14:59,290
Well...sorry.

1542
01:14:59,374 --> 01:15:01,501
What's that?

1543
01:15:03,044 --> 01:15:04,671
The Big Dipper?

1544
01:15:04,754 --> 01:15:07,048
Where are you looking?
What, here?

1545
01:15:07,090 --> 01:15:08,216
Over here.

1546
01:15:08,299 --> 01:15:09,426
- This one?
- Yeah.

1547
01:15:11,594 --> 01:15:13,596
Uh...

1548
01:15:13,638 --> 01:15:15,098
I don't know.

1549
01:15:15,140 --> 01:15:17,684
All right.

1550
01:15:17,767 --> 01:15:19,227
Unh!

1551
01:15:19,310 --> 01:15:22,772
This is what I want.

1552
01:15:22,814 --> 01:15:26,276
Everyone's worried
about your mother...

1553
01:15:26,317 --> 01:15:27,777
and what she wants.

1554
01:15:27,819 --> 01:15:30,572
But for me...

1555
01:15:30,655 --> 01:15:33,116
this is enough.

1556
01:15:33,158 --> 01:15:37,912
Sitting down.

1557
01:15:37,996 --> 01:15:40,206
- Well, sounds crazy, doesn't it?
- No, no, no.

1558
01:15:40,290 --> 01:15:43,501
But I swear, I think that's it.

1559
01:15:43,585 --> 01:15:45,962
All my life working...

1560
01:15:46,004 --> 01:15:48,757
saving, building.

1561
01:15:48,840 --> 01:15:53,803
For what? All I ever wanted
really was to...

1562
01:15:53,845 --> 01:15:55,805
sit down...

1563
01:15:55,847 --> 01:15:57,932
not worry about anything.

1564
01:15:58,016 --> 01:16:00,769
Oh, boy, I get it.

1565
01:16:00,852 --> 01:16:03,396
Believe me, I get it.

1566
01:16:06,316 --> 01:16:08,902
You know what?

1567
01:16:08,985 --> 01:16:12,447
I think that's all
Mom wanted, too.

1568
01:16:14,324 --> 01:16:18,620
Only she wanted to sit next to you.

1569
01:16:24,167 --> 01:16:26,419
You're a nice guy,
you know that?

1570
01:16:26,503 --> 01:16:29,589
Ah, that's the tequila talking.

1571
01:16:29,673 --> 01:16:34,094
No. No, you're a nice fella.

1572
01:16:34,177 --> 01:16:35,929
Ahh.

1573
01:16:36,012 --> 01:16:40,684
Thanks for being my baby boy.

1574
01:16:42,519 --> 01:16:44,938
I heard you with your girl.

1575
01:16:45,021 --> 01:16:47,482
I think you got it right.

1576
01:16:47,524 --> 01:16:51,444
I mean, a baby
comes into the world.

1577
01:16:51,528 --> 01:16:55,448
Where's it gonna go?
It could go anywhere, right?

1578
01:16:55,532 --> 01:16:58,952
You could've gone
to some parents in China...

1579
01:16:59,035 --> 01:17:01,788
or Timbuktu,
but you didn't.

1580
01:17:01,871 --> 01:17:03,957
You came to us.

1581
01:17:04,040 --> 01:17:06,876
Why? Who the hell knows?

1582
01:17:06,960 --> 01:17:10,505
But it worked out good.

1583
01:17:14,467 --> 01:17:18,221
Well, thanks for being my daddy.

1584
01:17:18,304 --> 01:17:19,931
My pleasure.

1585
01:17:24,811 --> 01:17:27,522
Well, I'll tell you...

1586
01:17:27,605 --> 01:17:30,900
all I ever really wanted...

1587
01:17:30,984 --> 01:17:32,444
really...

1588
01:17:38,324 --> 01:17:40,452
pretty much this.

1589
01:18:36,966 --> 01:18:38,468
Benny?

1590
01:18:45,308 --> 01:18:46,601
Benny?

1591
01:18:59,781 --> 01:19:02,283
Well, if that's camping...

1592
01:19:02,325 --> 01:19:05,078
I can do without it.

1593
01:19:09,457 --> 01:19:11,626
What?

1594
01:19:12,961 --> 01:19:15,714
Her doctors discovered it
two weeks ago.

1595
01:19:15,797 --> 01:19:18,091
Told her it was inoperable.

1596
01:19:18,174 --> 01:19:21,803
They said,
''Figure six months.''

1597
01:19:21,845 --> 01:19:25,724
I don't understand.
I mean, how can that be?

1598
01:19:25,807 --> 01:19:28,059
She didn't tell anyone.
She didn't--she didn't--

1599
01:19:28,143 --> 01:19:30,979
she didn't even tell the girls
till she was at the hospital already.

1600
01:19:31,021 --> 01:19:32,397
She went out to the island...

1601
01:19:32,480 --> 01:19:34,232
and she found some nice
little place on the water...

1602
01:19:34,315 --> 01:19:35,400
and she was--

1603
01:19:35,483 --> 01:19:37,402
she was by herself
for a couple of days.

1604
01:19:37,485 --> 01:19:39,404
She was feeling fine.

1605
01:19:39,487 --> 01:19:43,450
And then she started--
she started blacking out.

1606
01:19:47,162 --> 01:19:49,247
Oh, my God.

1607
01:19:49,330 --> 01:19:52,083
Oh, my God.

1608
01:19:52,167 --> 01:19:57,088
So, when she wrote that note
on the refrigerator...

1609
01:19:57,172 --> 01:19:58,506
she made that all up?

1610
01:19:58,548 --> 01:20:01,092
No, she didn't make it up.

1611
01:20:01,176 --> 01:20:02,761
She did want to be alone.

1612
01:20:02,844 --> 01:20:05,764
Just for reasons...

1613
01:20:05,847 --> 01:20:08,058
nobody knew about.

1614
01:20:10,018 --> 01:20:12,312
How could this be?

1615
01:21:40,984 --> 01:21:44,320
Hello, my busy playboys.

1616
01:21:46,322 --> 01:21:49,659
Heh! Hello.

1617
01:21:55,040 --> 01:21:57,000
All right. All right.

1618
01:21:57,042 --> 01:21:58,793
Look at you.

1619
01:21:58,877 --> 01:22:01,338
You don't need
to be so dramatic.

1620
01:22:01,379 --> 01:22:03,298
I'm not going anywhere yet.

1621
01:22:03,340 --> 01:22:04,924
And come here.

1622
01:22:09,137 --> 01:22:10,430
How are you?

1623
01:22:10,513 --> 01:22:12,390
Better than you.

1624
01:22:12,474 --> 01:22:14,768
What did the doctor say?

1625
01:22:14,851 --> 01:22:16,936
Oh, the doctor.

1626
01:22:17,020 --> 01:22:18,938
He said I'm an old lady...

1627
01:22:19,022 --> 01:22:21,983
and this is what happens
to old ladies.

1628
01:22:23,693 --> 01:22:26,029
Why wouldn't you tell me?

1629
01:22:26,112 --> 01:22:28,239
You think I tell you everything?

1630
01:22:29,866 --> 01:22:32,452
You know, you think
you're gonna live forever...

1631
01:22:32,535 --> 01:22:33,953
but you don't.

1632
01:22:34,037 --> 01:22:37,707
Just live till one day,
and then suddenly...

1633
01:22:37,791 --> 01:22:39,793
you're done.

1634
01:22:39,876 --> 01:22:42,837
That's their big forever.

1635
01:22:42,879 --> 01:22:45,131
Oh, you got more visitors.

1636
01:22:45,215 --> 01:22:47,967
Charlene, this is
my husband, my son.

1637
01:22:48,051 --> 01:22:50,553
Now you know everyone.

1638
01:22:50,637 --> 01:22:53,807
All right,
give a girl some privacy.

1639
01:22:53,890 --> 01:22:54,849
Yeah, yeah.

1640
01:22:57,394 --> 01:22:58,687
All righty, then.

1641
01:23:00,563 --> 01:23:02,524
Let's see if we can get you...

1642
01:23:12,992 --> 01:23:14,953
Oh, wow, you guys drove fast.

1643
01:23:15,036 --> 01:23:16,162
- Ohh!
- Ohh!

1644
01:23:16,246 --> 01:23:17,580
Oh, it's nice to see you.

1645
01:23:17,664 --> 01:23:18,915
Hi. Mwah.

1646
01:23:18,998 --> 01:23:20,417
- Mwah.
- Hi.

1647
01:23:20,458 --> 01:23:22,419
Hey, look who's here.

1648
01:23:22,502 --> 01:23:23,628
Hey. Hi. How are you?

1649
01:23:23,712 --> 01:23:26,673
Hello, gorgeous girl.
How are you, honey?

1650
01:23:26,756 --> 01:23:27,716
Good to see you.

1651
01:23:27,799 --> 01:23:28,758
- Hi.
- Hi.

1652
01:23:28,842 --> 01:23:30,927
- Hey.
- Hi, sweetheart. How are you?

1653
01:23:31,011 --> 01:23:32,762
Sit down, darling.

1654
01:23:32,846 --> 01:23:34,931
So, how was the farm?

1655
01:23:35,015 --> 01:23:36,099
What farm?

1656
01:23:36,182 --> 01:23:38,727
They went to look at a house,
a farmhouse on a lake.

1657
01:23:38,768 --> 01:23:40,395
Nobody tells me anything.

1658
01:23:40,437 --> 01:23:41,938
So was it nice?

1659
01:23:42,022 --> 01:23:43,189
I don't want to talk about it.

1660
01:23:43,273 --> 01:23:46,943
Hey, this place didn't work out,
but let me say this.

1661
01:23:47,027 --> 01:23:50,280
This guy is gonna find you a farm.

1662
01:23:50,363 --> 01:23:51,781
I promise you that.

1663
01:23:51,865 --> 01:23:54,492
- I don't want a farm.
- What does that mean?

1664
01:23:54,576 --> 01:23:56,411
- We need to live in the country?
- Yeah.

1665
01:23:56,453 --> 01:23:58,538
Oh, you know that
I've never wanted that.

1666
01:23:58,621 --> 01:24:00,206
Don't you?

1667
01:24:00,290 --> 01:24:02,334
Your mother wanted that.

1668
01:24:02,417 --> 01:24:04,085
Not--not me.

1669
01:24:04,127 --> 01:24:07,922
No, I know. I know she--

1670
01:24:07,964 --> 01:24:09,591
What are you saying?

1671
01:24:09,632 --> 01:24:11,343
So...you "don't" want it?

1672
01:24:11,426 --> 01:24:13,386
Sorry.

1673
01:24:13,470 --> 01:24:15,513
Wrong wife.

1674
01:24:15,597 --> 01:24:17,932
So when--when we're
looking every Sunday...

1675
01:24:17,974 --> 01:24:19,768
in the magazine section
and you're pointing...

1676
01:24:19,809 --> 01:24:21,269
and you're pointing it out,
what is that?

1677
01:24:21,311 --> 01:24:24,856
Well, it seemed
so important to you.

1678
01:24:24,939 --> 01:24:27,734
How come you never
mentioned this before?

1679
01:24:27,817 --> 01:24:29,319
Oh, I have.

1680
01:24:29,402 --> 01:24:32,113
You just haven't listened.

1681
01:24:33,156 --> 01:24:34,449
Ahem.

1682
01:24:45,919 --> 01:24:48,672
You know,
Benny showed me that letter.

1683
01:24:48,755 --> 01:24:51,466
What letter?

1684
01:24:51,508 --> 01:24:52,884
This letter.

1685
01:24:57,347 --> 01:24:59,974
- Where did you get this?
- Benny.

1686
01:25:00,016 --> 01:25:01,893
What happened?
What did I do now?

1687
01:25:01,976 --> 01:25:04,813
I always wondered
where this went to.

1688
01:25:04,854 --> 01:25:07,148
This one took it.

1689
01:25:07,190 --> 01:25:10,735
I thought maybe I threw it
in the garbage or something.

1690
01:25:10,819 --> 01:25:13,488
Wait a minute.
Wait a minute.

1691
01:25:13,530 --> 01:25:14,906
Wait a minute.

1692
01:25:14,989 --> 01:25:18,576
You said a lot of things
in this letter.

1693
01:25:18,660 --> 01:25:23,039
And I want you to know that...

1694
01:25:23,123 --> 01:25:26,459
I didn't know.

1695
01:25:27,794 --> 01:25:30,213
And now that you know?

1696
01:25:30,296 --> 01:25:33,591
Oh, now that I know?

1697
01:25:33,675 --> 01:25:36,428
Now that I know, I feel...

1698
01:25:36,511 --> 01:25:40,932
I feel bad.
What do you think?

1699
01:25:41,016 --> 01:25:43,435
I feel shitty.

1700
01:25:43,518 --> 01:25:47,022
Listen, don't believe
everything you read.

1701
01:25:47,063 --> 01:25:48,940
What? What are you do--

1702
01:25:49,024 --> 01:25:50,900
What--what--what--
what are you saying?

1703
01:25:52,193 --> 01:25:53,153
What?

1704
01:25:53,236 --> 01:25:56,906
What, you didn't mean
what you wrote in the letter?

1705
01:25:56,990 --> 01:25:58,616
Well...

1706
01:25:58,700 --> 01:25:59,951
Hmm?

1707
01:26:00,035 --> 01:26:03,955
Maybe...then.

1708
01:26:04,039 --> 01:26:05,874
- Then.
- Then.

1709
01:26:05,957 --> 01:26:07,709
Yeah. How about now?

1710
01:26:07,792 --> 01:26:11,254
How about all the years
between then and now?

1711
01:26:11,296 --> 01:26:12,881
- Benny. What are you doing?
- Wait.

1712
01:26:12,964 --> 01:26:14,299
Wait a second.
Wait a second.

1713
01:26:14,382 --> 01:26:16,551
People change.

1714
01:26:16,634 --> 01:26:18,178
You know.

1715
01:26:18,261 --> 01:26:20,388
No, that's not true.

1716
01:26:20,472 --> 01:26:21,931
No, people don't change.

1717
01:26:21,973 --> 01:26:24,642
They change their expectations.

1718
01:26:24,726 --> 01:26:26,436
They adjust.

1719
01:26:26,519 --> 01:26:29,230
What?

1720
01:26:29,272 --> 01:26:31,733
Have I felt disappointed? Yes.

1721
01:26:31,775 --> 01:26:33,610
All right?

1722
01:26:33,693 --> 01:26:36,237
Do I wish some things
had gone better?

1723
01:26:36,321 --> 01:26:39,407
Of course, yes, I wish
some things had gone better.

1724
01:26:39,491 --> 01:26:42,035
So, who gets
everything they want?

1725
01:26:44,454 --> 01:26:46,664
OK. All right.

1726
01:26:46,748 --> 01:26:48,416
What do you want me to say?

1727
01:26:48,458 --> 01:26:49,793
Say what you want to say.

1728
01:26:51,586 --> 01:26:53,963
What are you saving it for?

1729
01:26:54,005 --> 01:26:56,549
Come on, he's a big boy.

1730
01:26:59,052 --> 01:27:01,388
Hmm?

1731
01:27:01,471 --> 01:27:03,598
Why did you leave him?

1732
01:27:03,682 --> 01:27:04,766
Truth.

1733
01:27:17,987 --> 01:27:20,573
I left...

1734
01:27:20,657 --> 01:27:24,285
because I wanted to see
if I could.

1735
01:27:32,502 --> 01:27:34,254
I wanted to--

1736
01:27:34,337 --> 01:27:37,549
to be not taken for granted.

1737
01:27:51,354 --> 01:27:53,023
Plus...

1738
01:27:53,106 --> 01:27:56,276
you know why else?

1739
01:27:56,359 --> 01:27:59,195
I know that when I'm gone--

1740
01:27:59,279 --> 01:28:00,947
heh--

1741
01:28:01,031 --> 01:28:04,117
you're not gonna know
what to do.

1742
01:28:04,200 --> 01:28:07,704
I don't think
you're so good by yourself.

1743
01:28:07,787 --> 01:28:10,206
This way, you could practice...

1744
01:28:10,290 --> 01:28:14,627
see what it's like, you know?

1745
01:28:14,711 --> 01:28:18,381
Heh. And if you
hated me for it...

1746
01:28:18,465 --> 01:28:20,550
that's not so terrible.

1747
01:28:20,633 --> 01:28:23,720
You'd all get to talk
about it together.

1748
01:28:36,483 --> 01:28:40,320
See, this is the thing
about my mother.

1749
01:28:40,403 --> 01:28:43,573
She was made of love.

1750
01:28:43,656 --> 01:28:45,200
In the middle of all this...

1751
01:28:45,241 --> 01:28:48,453
she was taking care
of everyone else.

1752
01:28:50,830 --> 01:28:53,124
Under all that anger...

1753
01:28:53,208 --> 01:28:55,752
after all that disappointment...

1754
01:28:55,835 --> 01:28:57,754
the flame still flickered...

1755
01:28:57,837 --> 01:28:59,964
the love kept ticking.

1756
01:29:05,261 --> 01:29:08,390
And she still held on to hope.

1757
01:29:08,431 --> 01:29:10,892
Despite everything she knew...

1758
01:29:10,934 --> 01:29:13,061
and even everything she said...

1759
01:29:13,103 --> 01:29:16,481
she chose to believe
that things really might change.

1760
01:29:19,526 --> 01:29:21,569
And my father--

1761
01:29:21,611 --> 01:29:23,446
God bless him--

1762
01:29:23,530 --> 01:29:26,950
to his credit
and to everyone's amazement...

1763
01:29:27,033 --> 01:29:29,077
he did manage to change.

1764
01:29:29,119 --> 01:29:33,123
He still had within him
the ability to surprise.

1765
01:29:35,125 --> 01:29:38,128
OK, you can look.

1766
01:29:45,135 --> 01:29:47,971
I heard you never got to go.

1767
01:29:52,308 --> 01:29:55,061
It's been closed for,
like, sixty years...

1768
01:29:55,145 --> 01:29:56,438
so, you know...

1769
01:29:56,479 --> 01:30:00,775
a lot of the best exhibits
aren't up anymore.

1770
01:30:00,817 --> 01:30:03,486
On the other hand...

1771
01:30:03,570 --> 01:30:07,490
on the other hand,
there's no lines.

1772
01:30:12,495 --> 01:30:15,957
Oh, almost forgot.

1773
01:30:15,999 --> 01:30:19,461
I got a little something for you.

1774
01:30:19,502 --> 01:30:23,631
What are you trying to do, kill me?

1775
01:30:40,315 --> 01:30:44,027
So it took me
fifty years to understand.

1776
01:30:44,110 --> 01:30:45,820
So?

1777
01:30:45,862 --> 01:30:49,324
I'm not the swiftest guy in town.

1778
01:30:49,366 --> 01:30:53,661
But now I'm all caught up,
what do you say we try again?

1779
01:30:53,703 --> 01:30:55,997
Round two.

1780
01:30:56,039 --> 01:30:58,833
We'll say round one
was everything up till now...

1781
01:30:58,875 --> 01:31:01,419
and round two
is from today on.

1782
01:31:01,503 --> 01:31:03,171
What do you think?

1783
01:31:03,213 --> 01:31:06,257
Sound like a plan to you?

1784
01:31:06,341 --> 01:31:08,468
Your loving husband, Sam.

1785
01:31:16,017 --> 01:31:17,310
OK.

1786
01:32:16,995 --> 01:32:19,581
My mother made it
through the summer.

1787
01:32:19,664 --> 01:32:21,958
That's how long forever
turned out to be.

1788
01:32:22,042 --> 01:32:24,336
But for that whole forever...

1789
01:32:24,419 --> 01:32:27,464
it was the happiest
I ever saw them together.

1790
01:32:29,841 --> 01:32:32,427
My father moved in with us
after that.

1791
01:32:32,510 --> 01:32:34,596
We had our grapefruit juice
every morning...

1792
01:32:34,679 --> 01:32:37,640
and watched the news
together every night.

1793
01:32:37,682 --> 01:32:40,143
It was a special, magical time.

1794
01:32:42,187 --> 01:32:44,939
But proving once again
that you never know...

1795
01:32:45,023 --> 01:32:48,610
we woke up one morning,
and my father didn't.

1796
01:32:48,693 --> 01:32:50,653
He had been feeling perfectly fine.

1797
01:32:50,695 --> 01:32:53,823
I think he just really missed his gal.

1798
01:32:53,907 --> 01:32:57,118
It was a year full of surprises.

1799
01:32:57,202 --> 01:32:59,662
A few months later,
we had another baby--

1800
01:32:59,704 --> 01:33:01,956
a boy.

1801
01:33:02,040 --> 01:33:06,127
We named him Martin Samuel,
after both of them.

1802
01:33:08,672 --> 01:33:11,257
The little guy never got to know
my mother and father...

1803
01:33:11,341 --> 01:33:14,678
but, as no love
shall heretofore be wasted...

1804
01:33:14,761 --> 01:33:18,640
I promise you,
he's gonna hear all about 'em.
